#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:643
msgid "Enhance this fortress"
msgstr "Mellora esta fortaleza"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:662
msgid "Enhance your fortress"
msgstr "Mellora a fortaleza"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:661
msgid "Enhance your fortress to a citadel"
msgstr "Converte a fortaleza nunha cidadela"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:656
msgid ""
"Enhance your fortress to a citadel now. Remember that you can speed time up\n"
"by using PAGE_UP, building a citadel takes a while."
msgstr ""
"Converte a fortaleza nunha cidadela agora. Lembra que podes facer que o "
"tempo\n"
"vaia máis a présa coa tecla Re Páx ─construír unha cidadela leva o seu─."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:663
msgid ""
"Enhance your fortress to a mighty citadel. The citadel can house 12 "
"soldiers\n"
"and is the biggest military building the barbarians can build. It also costs "
"a\n"
"lot and takes a long time to build. It is most suited to guard "
"strategically\n"
"important points like constricted points or mountains."
msgstr ""
"Converte a túa fortaleza nunha resistente cidadela. Unha cidadela pode\n"
"albergar unha ducia de soldados e trátase da instalación militar máis\n"
"grande dos bárbaros. Os seus custos son elevados, e construíla leva\n"
"un tempo ademais. Cómpre construíla en zonas de especial importancia\n"
"estratexia como puntos estreitos ou montañas."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:644
msgid "Enhancing buildings"
msgstr "Mellorar edificios"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:635
msgid ""
"Evade is the chance that the soldier is able to dodge an attack. It is 25% "
"for\n"
"a level 0 evade barbarian and increases in steps of 15% for each level."
msgstr ""
"Os soldados teñen unha certa probabilidade de esquivar os ataques. No\n"
"nivel cero é do 25% para os bárbaros, e aumenta un 15% por cada nivel."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:634
msgid "Evade:"
msgstr "Esquivar:"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:260
msgid "Everything can be built on the green house symbol."
msgstr "No símbolo da casa verde pode construírse de todo."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:262
msgid ""
"Everything except for big buildings can be built on a yellow house symbol."
msgstr ""
"No símbolo da casa amarela pode construírse de todo menos edificios grandes."

# O artigo déixase para a segunda parte da cadea, para dar liberdade á tradución.
#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:294
msgid ""
"Excellent! Directly after you placed a building, you are in road building\n"
"mode. The new road will start at the flag in front of your newly placed\n"
"construction site. You can enter road building mode for any flag by\n"
"left-clicking on a flag and selecting"
msgstr ""
"Perfecto! En canto comezas unha obra entras no modo de construción\n"
"de camiños. O novo camiño partirá da obra. Podes activar o modo de\n"
"construción de camiños dende calquera bandeira premendo nela e\n"
"premendo logo"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:429
msgid ""
"Excellent. By the way: closing windows in Widelands is as easy as\n"
"right-clicking on them. This works with all windows except for story "
"message\n"
"windows like this one. Go ahead and try it. First, close this window by "
"pressing\n"
"the button below, then right click into the messages window to close it."
msgstr ""
"Xenial. Por certo, pechar fiestras en Widelands é tan doado como\n"
"premer nelas co botón esquerdo do rato. Isto é aplicable a todas as\n"
"fiestras menos ás de mensaxes da narración, coma esta. Próbao.\n"
"Primeiro pecha esta fiestra premendo o botón que se amosa a\n"
"continuación, e logo preme co botón dereito do rato na fiestra de\n"
"mensaxes para pechala."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:227
msgid ""
"Excellent. Now there is a faster way to move, using the mouse instead: "
"Simply\n"
"right-click-and-hold anywhere on the map, then drag the mouse and instead\n"
"of the cursor, the view will be moved. Try it."
msgstr ""
"Moi ben. Hai unha forma máis rápida de desprazarte: utilizando o rato.\n"
"Deixa premido o botón dereito do rato en calquera parte do mapa, e ao\n"
"mover o rato, en vez de o cursor, o que se moverá será o mapa. Próbao."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:191
msgid ""
"Excellent. The lumberjack's hut is done. A lumberjack will now move in and\n"
"start chopping down trees, so our trunks income is secured for now. Now on "
"to\n"
"the raw stone."
msgstr ""
"Excelente. A cabana do leñador xa está construída. Agora o leñador irá a "
"ela\n"
"e comezará pinchar árbores, así que de momento temos asegurada a reserva\n"
"de troncos. Agora a pedra en bruto."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:477
msgid ""
"Expanding is as simple as building a military building at the corner of\n"
"your territory. The barbarians have a few different military buildings:\n"
"sentries, barriers, donjons, fortresses and citadels. The bigger\n"
"the building, the more expensive it is to build, the more land it conquers\n"
"around itself and the more soldiers can be stationed there. The buildings "
"also\n"
"vary in their vision range: buildings with a tower see farther than others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:470
msgid "Expanding your territory!"
msgstr "Expandir o territorio!"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:121
msgid ""
"First, I'll left-click on the symbol where I want the lumberjack's hut to "
"be\n"
"built. A window will appear where I can choose between buildings. Because "
"I'll\n"
"click a yellow house symbol - which means that its field can house medium "
"and small\n"
"buildings - I am presented with all the medium buildings that I can build. "
"The\n"
"lumberjack's hut is a small building so I will go on to select the small "
"buildings\n"
"tab. Then I'll choose the lumberjack's hut.\n"
"Click the \"OK\" button to watch me. I'll go really slow: I will click - "
"then select\n"
"the tab - and finally I'll choose the building."
msgstr ""
"Primeiro vou premer co botón esquerdo do rato no símbolo onde quero\n"
"que se constrúa a cabana do leñador. Aparecerá unha fiestra na que\n"
"poderei elixir entre os distintos edificios. Como vou premer nun símbolo\n"
"de casa amarelo ─que significa que se poden construír edificios pequenos\n"
"e medianos─, apareceranme todos os edificios medianos que podo\n"
"construír. Como a cabana do leñador é un edificio pequeno, irei á\n"
"lingüeta destes. Unha vez nela escollerei a cabana do leñador. Para verme\n"
"preme no botón de «aceptar». Irei moi a modo: premerei, escollerei a\n"
"lingüeta, e logo escollerei o edificio."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:498
msgid ""
"For a full-fledged economy, we need coal, iron and gold. These can be found\n"
"in mountains. Conquer some area on the mountains to the south-west of your\n"
"headquarters by building some military buildings close to your border."
msgstr ""
"Para termos unha economía completa necesitamos carbón, ferro e ouro. Estes\n"
"atópanse nas montañas. Conquista algunha zona nas montañas que hai ao\n"
"suroeste do cuartel xeral construíndo algunha instalación militar preto da "
"fronteira."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:200
msgid "Getting a quarry up."
msgstr "Construír unha canteira."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:240
msgid "Great. Now about that quarry..."
msgstr "Xenial. Agora, acerca da canteira..."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:391
msgid ""
"Hi, it's me again! This time, I sent you a message. Messages are sent to "
"you\n"
"by Widelands to inform you about important events: empty mines, attacks on "
"your\n"
"tribe, won or lost military buildings, resources found..."
msgstr ""
"Boas, son eu de novo! Desta vez envíoche unha mensaxe. Widelands\n"
"envíache mensaxes para informarte de eventos importantes: minas baleiras,\n"
"ataques, conquistas ou perdas de instalacións militares, descubrimento de\n"
"recursos, etc."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:620
msgid "Hitpoints:"
msgstr "Vida:"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:248
msgid "How to build a quarry"
msgstr "Construír unha canteira"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:43
msgid ""
"I am sorry, but I have to rip this again. We might need the space here "
"later\n"
"on. If I am too slow for you, you might want to play a real game and just "
"find\n"
"everything out for yourself. Otherwise, please bear with me, I am not the\n"
"youngest and quickest anymore."
msgstr ""
"Síntoo, pero temos que tirala de novo. Máis tarde poderiamos necesitar\n"
"o espazo. Se vou lento de máis para ti, ao mellor deberías xogar unha\n"
"partida de verdade e ir descubrindo as cousas pola túa conta. Senón,\n"
"ten paciencia comigo, que xa me pesan os anos."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:675
msgid ""
"I created a sparring partner for you: It is an empire tribe close to your\n"
"citadel. To attack its buildings, click on the door of your target "
"building,\n"
"choose the number of soldiers that you wish to send and click on the attack\n"
"button. Your soldiers will come from all nearby military buildings. "
"Likewise,\n"
"the defenders will come from all nearby military buildings of the enemy and\n"
"intercept your forces."
msgstr ""
"Creeiche un contrincante. Trátase dunha tribo imperial que está preto da\n"
"túa cidadela. Para atacar as súas instalacións, preme na súa porta, escolle\n"
"a cantidade de soldados que queres enviar atacala e preme no botón de\n"
"«atacar». Os teus soldados sairán das instalacións militares das\n"
"proximidades. Do mesmo xeito, das instalacións militares inimigas dos\n"
"arredores sairán defensores que se enfrontarán ás túas forzas."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:645
msgid ""
"I will create an enemy for you soon, but let's make sure you are prepared.\n"
"This fortress is already quite strong and conquers a lot of space. But there "
"is\n"
"an even bigger building: the citadel."
msgstr ""
"Dentro de pouco creareiche un inimigo, así que preparémoste para facerlle\n"
"fronte. Esta fortaleza xa é bastante forte e conquista moito espazo. Pero\n"
"existe unha instalación aínda maior, a cidadela."

# A esta cadea seguirá algo como «o botón de blablabla»,
#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:301
msgid ""
"If you decide you do not want to build a road at this time, you can cancel\n"
"road building by clicking on the starting flag of the road and selecting"
msgstr ""
"Se prefires non construír un camiño nestes momentos, podes cancelar\n"
"a súa construción premendo a bandeira onde comeza e logo"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:268
msgid ""
"If you place something on a field, the surrounding fields might have less\n"
" space for holding buildings, so choose your fields wisely."
msgstr ""
"Se pos algo nunha zona, as zonas que a rodean poderían ver reducido\n"
"o seu espazo e por tanto a diversidade de edificios que se poden construír\n"
"nelas, así que escolle coidadosamente."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:583
msgid ""
"If you want to come back to this south-western part of your realm, just "
"scroll here\n"
"via right-button scrolling or open the minimap by clicking on the"
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:388
msgid "Introducing messages"
msgstr "Introdución ás mensaxes"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:95
msgid ""
"It is easier to understand what is allowed to be built on which field when\n"
"the build help symbols are enabled. Do so now either by pressing SPACE or "
"by\n"
"clicking the fourth button from the left at the very bottom of the screen.\n"
"Click the \"OK\" button and then give it a try."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:283
msgid ""
"Just click on any house symbol next to the stones, select the small "
"buildings\n"
"tab in the window that opens up, then click on the quarry symbol."
msgstr ""
"Preme en calquera símbolo de casa que haxa preto das rochas, escolle\n"
"a lingüeta dos edificios pequenos na fiestra que apareza, e preme no\n"
"símbolo da canteira."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:338
msgid ""
"Keep the slopes in mind while placing roads and use them to your advantage.\n"
"Also try to keep roads as short as possible and always remember to place as\n"
"many flags as you can on road segments to share the load better."
msgstr ""
"Ten en conta os desniveis á hora de construír camiños e aprovéitaos. "
"Procura\n"
"ademais facer os camiños o máis curtos posible e divide mellor a súa carga\n"
"facendo bandeiras neles."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:88
msgid "Left-click the \"OK\" button to close this box and then try it."
msgstr ""
"Preme co botón dereito do rato no botón de «aceptar» para pechar esta caixa, "
"e logo próbao."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:371
msgid ""
"Let me quickly enable those two for you. Remember: 'c' and 's' are the "
"keys.\n"
"Alternatively you can click on any field without a building on it, select "
"the\n"
"watch tab and then click on the corresponding buttons."
msgstr ""
"Déixame que chos active eu nun intre. Lémbrao, as teclas son «C» e «S».\n"
"Tamén podes premer nunha zona sen edificio, escoller a lingüeta de "
"vixilancia\n"
"e logo premer nos botóns correspondentes."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:68
msgid "Let's dive right in!"
msgstr "Mergullémonos!"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:520
msgid ""
"Let's search for resources in this mountain.  First, we'll build a road "
"into\n"
"the mountains and place a flag. Then, we click on the flag and call a "
"geologist\n"
"to it. I'll show you how it's done."
msgstr ""
"Busquemos recursos na montaña. Primeiro construiremos un camiño\n"
"ás montañas e poremos unha bandeira. Logo premeremos nela e\n"
"chamaremos a un xeólogo. Ensinareiche."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:489
msgid ""
"Let's try it out now: Build a few military buildings on your south western\n"
"border.  We want to capture some of this mountain, so we can search for\n"
"resources there. Bigger buildings will conquer more land which can be "
"beneficial\n"
"close to mountains because you can't build houses in mountains."
msgstr ""
"Agora probémolo. Constrúe algunhas instalacións militares na túa fronteira\n"
"suroeste. O obxectivo e facerse con parte da montaña para poder buscar\n"
"recursos nela. Canto maiores sexan as instalacións, maior será o territorio\n"
"conquistado, o que pode resultar beneficioso preto das montañas dado\n"
"que nelas non se poden construír casas."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:549
msgid "Let's wait and see what the geologist finds on the mountain."
msgstr "Agardemos a ver que atopa o xeólogo na montaña."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:188
msgid "Lumberjack is done"
msgstr "Rematouse a construción da cabana do leñador"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:104
msgid "Lumberjack's spot"
msgstr "Fogar do leñador"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:460
msgid "Message arrived!"
msgstr "Hai unha nova mensaxe!"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:389
msgid "Messages"
msgstr "Mensaxes"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:556
msgid "Mining conclusion"
msgstr "Rematou a mina"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:213
msgid "Move your view with the cursor keys"
msgstr "Move a vista coas teclas de frecha"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:233
msgid "Move your view with the mouse"
msgstr "Move a vista co rato"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:214
msgid "Moving your view"
msgstr "Mover a vista"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:215
msgid ""
"Moving your view is essential to get a complete overview of your whole\n"
"economy. There are two ways to move your view in Widelands. The first one "
"is\n"
"to use the cursor keys on your keyboard. The second one is the more common "
"and\n"
"faster one: press-and-hold the right mouse button anywhere on the map, then "
"move\n"
"your mouse around and you'll see the view scroll."
msgstr ""
"Para obter unha visión global da túa economía resulta imprescindible\n"
"mover a vista. En Widelands podes mover a vista de dúas maneiras. Unha\n"
"é utilizar as teclas de frecha. A outra ─máis habitual e rápida─ consiste "
"en\n"
"manter premido o botón dereito do rato nalgunha parte do mapa e movelo."

# Habería que descubrir o contexto e traducir en consecuencia.
#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:41
msgid "Nice and easy does it all the time"
msgstr "Está ben e faino todo o tempo"

# A cadea seguirá probablemente con outra como «o botón de blablabla».
#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:160
msgid ""
"Nice how they work, isn't it? But the poor carrier has a very long way to "
"go.\n"
"We can make it easier for him (and more efficient for us) when we place "
"another\n"
"blue flag on the road. You try it this time: click on the yellow flag "
"symbol\n"
"in between the two blue flags we just placed and then click on the"
msgstr ""
"Traballan ben, non si? Pero ao pobre transportador lle espera un longo\n"
"camiño. Podemos facilitarlle a tarefa construíndo outra bandeira azul no\n"
"camiño, aumentando así a súa eficiencia. Esta vez probaralo ti. Preme\n"
"no símbolo da casa amarela que hai entre as dúas bandeiras azuis que\n"
"acabamos de poñer e preme"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:563
msgid ""
"Note that a mine needs rations to work. Rations are\n"
"produced in taverns and taverns need meat, pitta bread, and fish to produce\n"
"them. You will need a lot more infrastructure to get your mines working\n"
"well. This infrastructure also varies from tribe to tribe. You'll get them\n"
"explained in the introduction campaigns for the three tribes."
msgstr ""
"Ten en conta que as minas necesitan racións para funcionar. Estas "
"prodúcense\n"
"nas tabernas, que necesitan á súa vez carne, pita e pescado para "
"producilas.\n"
"Para que as túas minas traballen ben necesitarás unha infraestrutura moito "
"maior.\n"
"Dita infraestrutura varía á súa vez entre as distintas tribos. "
"Explicaráseche nas\n"
"campañas de introdución a cada unha delas."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:271
msgid ""
"Now go ahead, try it. The quarry is a small building, so if you click on a\n"
"medium or big building symbol, you will have to select the small buildings\n"
"tab first to find it. Go on, check it out!"
msgstr ""
"Agora dálle, próbao. A canteira é un edificio pequeno, así que se premes\n"
"nun símbolo de edificio mediano ou grande, terás que escoller a lingüeta\n"
"dos edificios pequenos e logo buscar o da canteira. Mírao, veña!"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:342
msgid ""
"Now please rebuild the road between your quarry and your headquarters.\n"
"We'll wait until the quarry is completed."
msgstr ""
"Agora volve construír o camiño entre a canteira e o teu cuartel xeral.\n"
"Agardaremos a que remate a súa construción."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:149
msgid ""
"Now watch closely as a builder leaves the headquarters and goes to the\n"
"construction site. Also a carrier will take position in between the two "
"blue\n"
"flags and carry wares from one blue flag to the other."
msgstr ""
"Agora fíxate en como o construtor sae do cuartel xeral e vai á obra. O\n"
"mesmo fará un transportador, que levará os materiais dunha bandeira\n"
"azul á outra."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:381
msgid "Now we know what's going on. Let's wait for this quarry to finish."
msgstr "Agora sabemos o que pasa. Agardemos a que remate a obra."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:306
msgid ""
"Now, about this road. Remember: we are already in road building mode since "
"you\n"
"just ordered the quarry. You can either make it longer by one field at a "
"time\n"
"by left-clicking multiple times on neighbouring fields for perfect control "
"over\n"
"the route the road takes like so:"
msgstr ""
"Agora falemos do camiño. Lembra que xa estamos no modo de construción\n"
"de camiños porque acabas de comezar a construción dunha canteira. Podes\n"
"ampliar o camiño tramo por tramo premendo continuamente co botón dereito\n"
"do rato nos puntos que arrodean o extremo do camiño para así ter un maior\n"
"control sobre o seu percorrido. Sería así:"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:515
msgid ""
"Okay, now we own some of the area on this mountain. Mountains are very\n"
"important, because they contain resources: coal, iron ore, gold ore and\n"
"granite.  Each tribe uses the resources differently, but all need mines to "
"get\n"
"the resources out of the ground."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:575
msgid ""
"On to the last topic now. We are going to talk about soldiers, their "
"training\n"
"and their profession: warfare. As mentioned, Widelands is about building "
"up,\n"
"not burning down: therefore warfare is also more focused on the economics "
"than\n"
"the military strategies. Nevertheless, warfare offers one way to challenge\n"
"other players and it has some game mechanics that deserve explanation. The\n"
"economies of the tribes are explained in their individual tutorial "
"campaigns.\n"
"Ok, I am going to create us a little training ground with a training camp "
"and a\n"
"warehouse to the north east of here."
msgstr ""
"E xa para rematar, falaremos dos soldados e de como adestralos para o\n"
"combate. Como xa se dixo, o obxectivo en Widelands é construír, non\n"
"destruír, polo que a guerra está máis centrada na estratexia económica\n"
"que na propiamente militar. Porén a guerra é unha forma de retar a outros\n"
"xogadores e consta dalgúns procedementos que cómpre describir. As\n"
"economías das tribos explícanse nas súas respectivas campañas de\n"
"aprendizaxe. Veña, crearei unha pequena zona de adestramento cun\n"
"campo de adestramento e un almacén ao nordeste de aquí."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:327
msgid ""
"One more thing: around the field where your road would end you can see\n"
"different markers. They have the following meaning:"
msgstr ""
"Unha cousa máis, arredor da zona onde remata o camiño pode haber\n"
"distintos marcadores. Estes teñen o seguinte significado:"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:238
msgid "Onward to the quarry"
msgstr "A pola canteira"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:225
msgid "Other ways to move the view"
msgstr "Outros xeitos de mover a vista"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:157
msgid "Placing another flag"
msgstr "Poñer outra bandeira"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:264
msgid "Red building symbols can only hold small buildings and flags."
msgstr ""
"Nos símbolos de casa vermellos só poden poñerse edificios pequenos e "
"bandeiras."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:292
#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:316
#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:325
msgid "Road building"
msgstr "Construción de camiños"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:513
msgid "Searching for resources"
msgstr "Buscar recursos"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:366
msgid ""
"Similar to this are building statistics which are also toggled via a\n"
"button on the watch tab of any field. The hotkey for it is 's'. This will\n"
"display an information string about the productivity of buildings or the\n"
"progress of construction sites."
msgstr ""
"De xeito parecido existen estatísticas dos edificios, que poden amosarse\n"
"premendo no botón correspondente da fiestra de vixilancia de calquera\n"
"zona. O seu atallo é a tecla «S». Amosará información sobre a produtividade\n"
"do edificio en cuestión ou sobre o progreso da obra."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:558
msgid ""
"So our geologist found a lot of coal on this mountain. You should therefore\n"
"build a coal mine here. Building a mine is like building a house. The build "
"help\n"
"symbol for where a mine can be built is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:574
msgid "Soldiers and Warfare"
msgstr "Os soldados e maila guerra"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:199
msgid "Some stones were found"
msgstr "Atopáronse algunhas rochas"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:202
msgid ""
"Stones can be mined in granite mines, but the easier way is to build a "
"quarry\n"
"next to some stones laying around. As it happens, there is a pile of them\n"
"laying just to the west (left) of your headquarters. I will teach you now "
"how to\n"
"move your view over there."
msgstr ""
"As rochas podes extraerse mediante minas de granito, pero a forma máis\n"
"doada de facelo é mediante canteiras, construídas preto das rochas.\n"
"Parece haber moita rocha ao oeste do cuartel xeral. Ensinareiche a mover\n"
"a vista alí."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:715
msgid ""
"Thanks for playing this tutorial. Enjoy Widelands and remember\n"
"to visit us at"
msgstr ""
"Grazas por xogar esta campaña de aprendizaxe. Goza do Widelands\n"
"e non esquezas visitarnos en"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:137
msgid ""
"That won't do yet. I still need to connect the lumberjack's hut to the\n"
"rest of my road network. After I ordered a construction site, I was\n"
"automatically put in road building mode, so all I have to do is click on "
"the\n"
"blue flag in front of my headquarters."
msgstr ""
"Iso non abondará. Aínda teño que conectar a cabana do leñador co\n"
"resto da rede de camiños. Tras comezar unha obra, entrei de maneira\n"
"automatica no modo de construción de camiños, así que o único que\n"
"teño que facer é premer na bandeira que hai fronte ao cuartel xeral."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:624
msgid ""
"The amount of damage a soldier inflicts upon a successful attack on the\n"
"enemy. A barbarian soldier with attack level 0 inflicts ~14 hitpoints "
"damage\n"
"when he succeeds to hit an enemy. For each attack level, he gains 7 damage."
msgstr ""
"A cantidade de dano que inflixe un soldado cada vez que lle acada a un\n"
"inimigo. Os soldados bárbaros de nivel cero en ataque inflixen ao redor\n"
"de 14 puntos de dano ao atinarlle a un inimigo. Este dano aumenta en\n"
"7 por cada nivel de ataque adicional."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:335
msgid ""
"The connection between the fields is extremely steep. The speed increase in\n"
"one direction is huge while the slowdown in the other is also substantial."
msgstr ""
"O tramo é moi empinado. A velocidade é moi elevada nunha dirección, e tamén\n"
"moito menor na oposta."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:531
msgid ""
"The geologist will arrive shortly to the flag and start investigating the\n"
"area in his surroundings. He will place the following markers for the "
"various\n"
"resources:"
msgstr ""
"O xeólogo chegará en nada á bandeira e comezará a súa investigación\n"
"da zona e mailos arredores. Este porá os seguintes marcadores de\n"
"recursos:"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:395
msgid ""
"The message window can be toggled by the button on the very right at the\n"
"bottom of the screen. This button also changes appearance if new messages "
"are\n"
"available, but there is also a bell sound played whenever you receive a new\n"
"message."
msgstr ""
"A fiestra das mensaxes pode pecharse co botón da dereita de todo da parte\n"
"inferior da pantalla. A aparencia do botón cambia ademais cando hai "
"mensaxes\n"
"novas, ademais de reproducirse un son."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:414
msgid ""
"The message window is central to fully controlling your tribe's fortune. "
"But\n"
"you get a lot of messages in a real game. To keep your head straight, you "
"should\n"
"try to keep the inbox empty. Archive all your messages in the inbox now. To "
"do\n"
"so, open the messages window by pressing 'n' or clicking the right most "
"button\n"
"at the very bottom of the screen. Then mark all messages by checking the "
"check\n"
"box in front of them. Then, click the archive all button"
msgstr ""
"A fiestra das mensaxes é moi importante á hora de controlar a fortuna\n"
"da tribo. Pero nunha partida real recíbense unha morea de mensaxes.\n"
"Para non perdes a cabeza, deberías procurar deixar a caixa de entrada\n"
"baleira. Agora arquiva todas as mensaxes da caixa de entrada. Para iso,\n"
"abre a fiestra das mensaxes, ben coa tecla «N» ben co botón da dereita\n"
"de todo que hai na parte inferior da pantalla. Logo marca a caixa ao carón\n"
"de cada mensaxe. A continuación, preme no botón de «arquivar»."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:589
msgid ""
"The minimap shows you the complete map in miniature. You can directly jump "
"to\n"
"any field by left-clicking on it. You can also toggle buildings, roads, "
"flags\n"
"and player indicators on and off inside the minimap."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:169
msgid ""
"The shorter your road segments are, the faster your wares will be "
"transported.\n"
"You should therefore make sure that your roads have as many flags as "
"possible.\n"
"Build a blue flag now in the middle of the road that connects your "
"headquarters\n"
"to your lumberjack's hut."
msgstr ""
"Canto máis curtos sexan os tramos dos camiños, máis axiña se\n"
"transportarán os materiais. Polo tanto deberías asegurarte de que\n"
"os camiños teñan tantas bandeiras como sexa posible. Agora pon\n"
"unha bandeira azul no camiño que conecta a cabana do leñador\n"
"co teu cuartel xeral."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:330
msgid ""
"The terrain is flat here. Your carriers will be very swift on this terrain."
msgstr ""
"Aquí o terreo está plano. Os transportadores moveranse con facilidade por "
"este terreo."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:621
msgid ""
"The total life of a soldier. A barbarian soldier starts with ~130 "
"hitpoints,\n"
"with each hitpoint level he gains 28 hitpoints."
msgstr ""
"A vida total do soldado. Os soldados bárbaros comezan con uns 130\n"
"puntos de vida, e por cada nivel de vida adicional conseguen outros\n"
"28 puntos."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:279
msgid ""
"There are some stones to the west of your headquarters. Build a quarry "
"right\n"
"next to them. The quarry is a small building like the lumberjack's hut. You\n"
"can therefore build it on any field that shows a red, yellow or green house\n"
"when the build help is enabled (Press SPACE for that)."
msgstr ""
"Hai algunhas rochas ao oeste do cuartel xeral. Constrúe unha canteira\n"
"canda elas. Ao igual que a cabana do leñador, a canteira é un edificio\n"
"pequeno. Por tanto, podes construír unha en calquera zona que teña\n"
"unha casa vermella, amarela ou verde co asistente de construción\n"
"activado ─preme [espazo] para activalo─."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:70
msgid ""
"There are three different tribes in Widelands: the barbarians, the empire "
"and\n"
"the atlanteans. All tribes have a different economy, strength and "
"weaknesses,\n"
"but the general gameplay is the same for all. We play the barbarians for now."
msgstr ""
"En Widelands hai tres tribos distintas: os bárbaros, o imperio e os "
"atlánticos.\n"
"Cada unha ten unha economía de seu, así como as súas propias fortalezas e\n"
"debilidades, pero en xeral a forma de xogo é común a todas elas. De momento\n"
"xogaremos cos bárbaros."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:207
msgid ""
"There are two ways to move your view. The first one is using the cursor "
"keys\n"
"on your keyboard. Go ahead and try this out.  Click the \"OK\" button and "
"then move\n"
"the view using the cursor keys"
msgstr ""
"Existen dúas formas de mover a vista. Unha é mediante as teclas de frecha.\n"
"Próbao. Preme o botón de «aceptar» e logo move a vista utilizando as\n"
"teclas de frecha."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:332
msgid ""
"There is a small slope to climb to reach this field. This means your\n"
"workers are faster walking downwards than they are walking upwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:472
msgid ""
"There is one more thing I'd like to teach you now: Expanding your "
"territory.\n"
"The place that we start with around our headquarters is barely enough for a\n"
"basic build infrastructure and we do not have access to mountains which we\n"
"need to mine minerals and coal. So we have to expand our territory."
msgstr ""
"Agora hai algo máis que me gustaría ensinarche: a expandir o teu "
"territorio.\n"
"O espazo co que comezamos ao redor do cuartel xeral apenas permite levantar\n"
"unha infraestrutura de edificios e non temos acceso ás montañas, que será\n"
"necesario para extraer minerais e carbón. Así que temos que expandir\n"
"o noso territorio."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:604
msgid ""
"There we go. Take a look at the soldiers that are on their way into our\n"
"trainings camp. They look different than normal workers: they have a health "
"bar\n"
"over their head that displays their remaining hitpoints and they have four\n"
"symbols which symbolize the individual soldier's current levels in the four\n"
"different categories hitpoints, attack, defense and evade."
msgstr ""
"Imos aló. Mira para os soldados que van ao campo de adestramento. A súa\n"
"aparencia é distinta da dos traballadores normais: teñen unha barra de "
"saúde\n"
"sobre a cabeza que amosa a vida que lles queda, e teñen catro símbolos que\n"
"indican o seu nivel nas distintas categorías ─vida, ataque, defensa e "
"esquivar─."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:108
msgid ""
"There you go. I will explain about all those symbols in a minute. First, "
"let\n"
"me show you how to make a lumberjack's hut and how to connect it with a "
"road.\n"
"There is a sweet spot for a lumberjack right next to those trees.  I'll "
"describe\n"
"the steps I will take and then ask you to click on the \"OK\" button for me "
"to\n"
"demonstrate."
msgstr ""
"Vamos. Nun minuto che explico o deses símbolos. Pero primeiro déixame\n"
"aprenderche a construír unha cabana de leñador e a conectala cun camiño.\n"
"O lugar ideal para a cabana dun leñador sería canda esas árbores.\n"
"Explicareiche os pasos que tes que dar e logo pedireiche que premas no\n"
"botón de «aceptar» para deixarme amosarcho."

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:699
msgid ""
"This concludes the tutorial. There is some stuff we have not covered here --"
"\n"
"we have not even built a single producing building even though producing "
"wares\n"
"is the most important thing in Widelands -- but you've learned the ropes. "
"You\n"
"can learn about the remaining stuff while you go through the individual "
"tribe's\n"
"introduction campaigns. Each consists of some scenarios explaining the "
"tribes\n"
"and their economy while introducing the background story of Widelands. Have "
"fun\n"
"playing!"
msgstr ""
"Con isto remata a aprendizaxe. Quedaron algunhas cousas sen dar ─a pesar\n"
"de que a produción de materiais é o máis importante do xogo non vimos\n"
"como construír os edificios necesarios─ pero con isto xa tes o básico. O\n"
"resto podes aprendelo nas campañas de introdución ás distintas tribos.\n"
"Estas consisten nunha serie de escenarios que explican as tribos e a\n"
"súa economía ao tempo que contan un pouco a historia tras o Widelands.\n"
"Pásao ben!"

#: ../../campaigns/tutorial01.wmf/scripting/texts.lua:602
msgid "Trainings camp and soldier stats"
msgstr "Os campos de adestramento e as estatísticas dos soldados"

